<div id="ways-to-prevent">
  <h1>So, we know the situation. How do we prevent it from worsening?</h1>
  <br>
  <h4>
    There are many ways to reverse or at least reduce the pace of climate
    change. Some of the most straightforward ones that can be carried out by
    every individual easily in everyday life:
  </h4>
  <br />
  <div class="hover-orbs">
    <div class="hover-orb">
      <div class="visible"><h5>Reduce usage of cars</h4></div>
      <div class="hidden">
        Take bicycles to work instead. It will help to decrease your carbon
        footprint and it's also a great way to stretch those muscles!
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hover-orb">
      <div class="visible"><h5>Harvest rainwater</h4></div>
      <div class="move-up hidden">
        Using home equipment, try to store rainwater. Spread awareness about
        importance of conservation of water; urge people to use water
        judiciously.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hover-orb">
      <div class="visible"><h5>Plant a tree</h4></div>
      <div class="hidden">
        This has all sorts of benefits for the environment - like reducing the
        CO<sub>2</sub> amount - and it gives you a pass time as well.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hover-orb">
      <div class="visible"><h5>Reduce meat intake</h4></div>
      <div class="hidden">
        Meat harvesting produces about 100 tonnes of methane, a deadly gas,
        every year. Reducing its intake will decrease the toxic amount.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br />
</div>

